		<div class="post" id="post-2697805">
		<div class="long">
			<div class="head">
									<div class="options">
						<a href="javascript:;" onclick="togglePostFold(event,2697805)" class="btn btn-default btn-small btn-sm">Fold</a>
					</div>
								<div class="title" id="post-title-2697805">
																		author post
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser deleted" data-id="2303803"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/common--images/avatars/default/a16.png" alt=""/>(account deleted)</span> <span class="odate time_1480137368 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">26 Nov 2016 05:16</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2697805">
									

<p><em>Unless otherwise stated, any graphics or images in my articles are made and/or taken by me.</em></p>
<p><em><sub>&quot;I couldn't breathe if I tried;</sub></em><br />
<em><sub>I lay my head on the floor</sub>,</em><br />
<em><sub>my beating heart wanting more.</sub></em><br />
<em><sub>But I'll keep it in and keep you out;</sub></em><br />
<em><sub>I'm drowning, I'm drowning.</sub></em><br />
<em><sub>I'm drowning, <a href="https://youtu.be/n106Qo0D948">I'm drowning.&quot;</a></sub></em></p>
<hr />
<p>In a post in <a href="/scp-2708">SCP-2708</a>'s comments, <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-1994045/scp-2708#post-2692891">I said:</a> &quot;Is reality what we perceive or what others perceive? If you yourself feel and see something as being real, and you believe it's real, couldn't you argue that it is real, even if observers disagree? Are the baseline parameters of reality personal or public?&quot; This tale aims to explore that, and is likely the conclusion of the Baby's Guide/2708 setting.<sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-4911-1" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnote-4911-1')">1</a></sup></p>
<p>I'm not a huge fan of the bixby character (she's one of my old characters from my 'personal canon' as we call it, and I was originally planning on not using her in anything on the site), and I tried to make her as minimally present as possible while still making her seem like at least a little more than just a plot device. I did however refrain from revealing her item number anywhere in the tale just in case I ever want to actually write her, but human skips are a pain in the ass to write as SCP articles, so I probably won't.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;show&nbsp;up-front&nbsp;explanation&nbsp;of&nbsp;events/spoilers</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;collapse</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>Firstly, you gotta read <a href="/scp-2708">SCP-2708</a> - it's part of the series, despite being an SCP article rather than a tale.</p>
<p>So, in <a href="/baby-s-first-guide-to-keter-class-anomalies-and-other-questi">Baby's Guide</a>, it's established through implication that Dr. ████ ███████ (Adam Leeward) got someone pregnant, and the note at the end implies that that person is in containment, and thus, he's in pretty deep shit. However, in <a href="/scp-2708">SCP-2708</a>, we see that &quot;subjects affected claim to be capable of full interaction with [2708-A] as if it were a human partner, up to and including realistic perception of facial feature details and general appearance, realistic perception of physical stimulation, and, in one case, even a perceived full-term pregnancy.&quot;</p>
<p>So basically, we have Leeward self-aware of the fact that he's attracted to Aline and we have him take the proper actions to prevent said attraction, but he's also been affected by 2708 for an indeterminate amount of time - long enough for him to convince himself that there's a baby coming - while this is going on, and he starts to see Aline in 2708-A and vice versa, until he's too confused to comprehend it and realizes something's completely off while staring at himself in the mirror.</p>
<p>The title is just a pun on the fact that he has trouble processing emotion - just like AWCY warned us regarding Foundation employees in 2708's end note.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>In summary: This won't be for everyone, for the little bit of NSFW content or for the length or for the sappiness or for anything otherwise, and I respect that. And for reviews, thank you to: &#8230;no one/everyone. We've got another coldpost on our hands, lads.</p>
<hr />
<p>Edit: If you notice the adult tag, yeah, there's one scene in there. Personally I don't think it's long enough or vulgar enough to warrant a warning at the top of the page (there are a few in the tag without warnings), but if anyone thinks otherwise please let me know.</p>
<div class="footnotes-footer">
<div class="title">Footnotes</div>
<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-4911-1"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-4911-1')">1</a>. And yes, I was trying to come up with a way to make this tale's title &quot;'Baby's First Guide to Safe-Class Anomalies' &amp; Other Questionable Documents Recovered from the Hard Drive of Dr. ████ ███████&quot; but it simply could not work for contextual and tonal reasons. Oh well.</div>
</div>

